quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,64,"Burn therein this Day, for that you used to disbelieve.{1}",footnotes:1:{36:64} See the footnote of {3:91}.
  36,65,"This Day, We shall seal up their mouths, and their hands will speak to Us, and their legs will bear witness to what they used to earn. (It is said that one’s left thigh will be the first to bear the witness). [Tafsir At-Tabarî,]"
  36,66,"And if it had been Our Will, We would surely have wiped out (blinded) their eyes, so that they would struggle for the Path, how then would they see?"
  37,49,"(Delicate and pure) as if they were (hidden) eggs (well) preserved."
  37,50,"Then they will turn to one another, mutually questioning."
  37,51,"A speaker of them will say: "
  38,28,"Shall We treat those who believe (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds as Mufsidûn (those who associate partners in worship with Allâh and commit crimes) on earth? Or shall We treat the Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2) as the Fujjâr (criminals, disbelievers, the wicked)?"
  38,29,"(This is) a Book (the Qur’ân) which We have sent down to you, full of blessings, that they may ponder over its Verses, and that men of understanding may remember."
  38,30,"And to Dâwûd (David) We gave Sulaimân (Solomon). How excellent a slave! Verily, he was ever oft-returning in repentance (to Us)!"
  39,13,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  39,14,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  39,15,"So worship what you like besides Him. Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "